⭐ FULL SUMMARY (Every detail included, no gaps)

The video is an interview with GATE AIR 1 (Shourya) discussing his exact strategies, routines, lessons, and mistakes. The host asks questions and he answers step-by-step.

1. Intro

He intentionally did not solve 2020+ PYQs until the last 20–30 days.

He kept them to simulate the real exam environment and check his rank.

2. Rapid Tips / Secrets
Secret 1 – Smart Hack

His biggest hack was using a strategy while giving the exam:

Solve easy questions first

Then medium questions

Then lengthy/difficult ones

Secret 2 – Lessons from Full-Length Tests

Time management is extremely important.

Never spend 10 minutes on a single stuck question.

If a question cannot be solved within 3 minutes, skip it.

3. Only Tip for Aptitude

If he prepared again from scratch, he would:

Focus on verbal aptitude

Because the only negative mark he got was from aptitude.

4. Daily Routine of AIR 1

6 AM: Wake up & study 1 hour

Take 8:52 AM train → 1.5 hours travel

College till 4:30–5 PM

Reach home 6:30 PM

Rest 1 hour

Study 7:30–10 PM, then 30–60 min after dinner

Total: 4–5 hours/day + learning in college

He also studied during train travel using PDFs.

5. How Many Hours Should One Study?

Depends on the person; no fixed rule.

